<h2>About Me</h2>

<p>
  My name is Ilias (pronounced “ee-lee-ahs” or “ee-ly-ahs”), and I’m a PhD student at The University of Edinburgh. I’m part of the <a href="https://vios.science/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Vios Science Lab</a> under the guidance of Prof. <a href="https://www.eng.ed.ac.uk/about/people/dr-sotirios-tsaftaris" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Sotos Tsaftaris</a> and Dr. <a href="https://smcdonagh.github.io/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Steven McDonagh</a>.
</p>

<p>
  Before embarking on my PhD, I completed my MSc in Computer Science at Athens University of Economics and Business (AUEB). I was supervised by Prof. <a href="https://www2.aueb.gr/users/ion/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Ion Androutsopoulos</a>. Furthermore, I had the opportunity to work as an Applied Machine Learning Researcher at <a href="https://helvia.ai/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">helvia.ai</a>, specializing in Natural Language Processing and Large Language Models.
</p>

<p>
  I’m also an active member of the <a href="http://nlp.cs.aueb.gr/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">NLP Group</a> at AUEB, where we conduct research in NLP and Machine Learning.
</p>

